Good morning, 
For about 1 year or more the updates are terrible on the mobile app, I’ve listed some here, but honestly, there are so many that I don’t even know where to start: 
- Dislikes removed
- Videos displayed horizontally and not vertically in the "videos" tab of the channels
- Can no longer sort videos from older to newer
- The “drag up for more accurate search” feature that abruptly stops the video when accidentally clicking on the playback bar 
- In dark mode, the red playback bar becomes white when the video is allowed to scroll, The video loading bar is no longer visible as it is also white and EVERY TIME you have to press the video to see where the white line and red line are, etc. 
I was also forced to go back to the white mode of youtube which is unpleasant for the eyes because too bright. I may be forgetting others, but honestly, we’re not close anymore. So I’d like to ask you, is this all editable for a disgruntled user like me or is it irreversible and we’re forced to go through like chickens in a pen in silence? I’m not even talking about youtube shorts that are simply an aberration in the sole purpose of competing with some other Chinese app for teens lacking dopamine. So I would like to know when all this is going to change and if it was possible to go back to an older version of youtube so as not to have to undergo these updates each more inconsistent than the other. With such decisions, it should not surprise you that long-time users like me will desert the platform for another. 

As I ask you to accept my warmest greetings, I thank you for having read this to me and I hope that you will reply as soon as possible. 

Have a great day.
